steps.instruction:
## HTML fragments

With HTMX the server returns HTML fragments, not full pages. A fragment is a partial HTML snippet with no `<html>` or `<body>` tag. HTMX takes the fragment and inserts it into the correct place on the page.

`templates/todos.html` is that fragment. It renders a list of todos using Jinja2 loops.

Jinja2 basics:
```html
{% if todos %}
  {% for todo in todos %}
    {{ todo.title }}
  {% endfor %}
{% else %}
  No todos yet.
{% endif %}
```

You can use daisyUI classes inside the fragment exactly as you would on a full page.

## Task

Create `templates/todos.html`. Show each todo as a styled row with the title and a delete button. Give each row `id="todo-{{ todo.id }}"` as HTMX will use this to remove single items later.

